on certain classes (haste items, or high int/wis low ac items, for instance).<br>
<br>
So... based on that, the red scale from Naggy is rolled on by basically all plate-wearing melle classes (the one's who can use the BP - which includes bards and warriors who need it for their epic as well).<br>
<br>
The white scale can be used by all/all - and is something of a quandry.  It has +9 int/wis and +75 mana, making it a great caster/priest cloak... yet it also has +25SvC and decent AC as cloaks go...  However, in light of the fact that there are other, much easier cloaks to obtain with similar AC and SvC (though not quite as good)... I tend to lean towards limiting rolls on the white scale to casters, priests, and bards as they are the classes that would benefit most from it.<br>
<br>
I have been asked a number of times why I don't limit scale rolls to those classes who need it for their epic only, and my response is generally this:<br>
<br>
As much as I hate to say it, if you are focused and intent on getting your epic, regardless of what class you are, you will probably never get it by going on CoG raids alone.  That being said, limiting rolls to only epic-classes would be taking away the possible advantage of other classes who could use the item the scale can produce.  It would also serve to give added benefit to those people who are part of larger guilds and alliances that are capable of getting them their epic more better chances on the scales... and quite frankly, the kind of people who would only come on raids for that reason are the kind of people I DON'T want on my raids. <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.
