<br>
As for people not wanting to make the armor with the scale because the scale is worth so much more... you are assuming that all CoG raiders basically sell the loot they win.  This is a false premise.<br>
<br>
Also, CoG is not the only group that allows non-epic classes to roll (and win) scales from Naggy and Vox.<br>
<br>
Now that we have a couple facts straight, let us begin a discussion about CoG vs epics:<br>
<br>
As I've said before, the KCoG is not a good place to get an epic weapon.  If that is your only intent, do yourself a favor and join an uber-guild or larger alliance that is capable of helping you get it.<br>
<br>
One of the main reasons I'm opposed to limiting scale rolls to only those classes who need them for epics is that there are members of those larger guilds and alliances that come on CoG raids... and well, I don't wanna make CoG raids a great place for epic-hunters to tag along just because it'll give them more chances to get what they need.  That is not the kind of person I want to attract to our raids.<br>
<br>
No one, as of yet, has seriously complained about our rolls on red scales (probably because the red scale seems to be so much more common).  So basically this discussion ends up being strictly about white scales from Vox... which are pretty rare.<br>
<br>
I have many a time considered limiting scale rolls to epic classes alone... the main problem I have with rules and policies like that is that they get away from the purpose of the KCoG.  We are not here to get epic weapons for everyone, we are not here to get planes armor for everyone, we are not here to let uber-guilders &quot;double-dip&quot; for rare items, we are, in short, NOT ABOUT THE LOOT.  We are about giving people who would not otherwise have a chance the opportunity to go places and see things they wouldn't normally have.<br>
<br>
Which is why discussions about who should get to roll on what tend to piss me off.  Because they are basically about squabbling over loot.  And that's not why I run these raids.  These kinds of discussions, in fact, are the thing that I hate most about running these raids.  Which is why, in general, I tend to follow the KCoG's overall loot policy:<br>
<br>
If you bleed for it and can use it, you can roll for it.<br>
<br>
So... here's where my thinking is right now:<br>
<br>
Limiting who rolls on the white scales tends to encourage loot-hunters to come to our raids alone, thus giving them the best chances at winning it.  This runs counter to everything that the KCoG is about.<br>
<br>
The cloak, as unlikely as it may be that someone would actually make it, is actually pretty good gear for almost any class.  It's good AC for a back slot item, has nice Int/Wis, and has very nice cold resistance.  So, under CoG's normal loot rules, everyone gets to roll.<br>
<br>
Now think about this: If you are a guild-member of good standing and/or you have lots of friends in the game (like a certain un-guilded, sexless drood <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), and one of your guild-mates or friends wins something that you need for your epic... chances are pretty good yer gonna get it in the end, right?<br>
<br>
So, here's where I'm going with this:  Opening up the scale rolls to everyone (maybe even the red scale?) would encourage folks that need the scale for their epic to try and bring as many friends and guild-mates as possible to CoG raids - this giving them more chances to &quot;win&quot; the scale in the end... sorta like buying more than one raffle ticket... the more people you bring, the more chances you get.<br>
<br>
That way, rather than encouraging people to come alone, we'd be encouraging people to come with a posse!  THAT is the kind of policy I like!<br>
<br>
So what's everyone think about that?<br>
<br>
Addendum: Paladin books will continue to be Paladin only - they're no drop and I don't wanna encourage multi-questing items on that scale...  besides, if I was going to make any chances in the Paly book policy it would be to &quot;Kommisar gets the next book Nagafen drops.  Period.&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.
